<item>
            <title>[LU-17449] ptlrpc_server_get_timeout use of obd_at_* with NULL obd is misguided</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17449</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;using obd_at* with NULL OBDs needlessly fills the logs with messages like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;00000100:00100000:2.0:1705647379.933449:0:24718:0:(service.c:3700:ptlrpc_server_get_timeout()) NULL obd
00000100:00100000:2.0:1705647379.933452:0:24718:0:(service.c:3701:ptlrpc_server_get_timeout()) NULL obd
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We probably can just directly fill in at_max / at_min there.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15426&quot; title=&quot;WBC2: it should not cause rename() failed when WBC is disabled&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-15426&quot;&gt;LU-15426&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/45598&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/45598&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
